{
  "text": "HE et al BLOOD, 11 OCTOBER 2012 \u2150 VOLUME 120, NUMBER 15 For personal use only. on May 29, 2017 . by guest www.bloodjournal.org From considered to be a marker associated with M2-like, proangiogenic macrophages in tumors. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] Interestingly, the expression of Tie2 rose significantly in colony macrophages over time ( Figure 4B ), suggesting that the endothelial-induced macrophages were polarized toward the M2 fate.",
